ment, as well as his subsequent achievements, including as Chancellor of Macquarie University, make him deserving of a State funeral.\", \"from\": 327, \"to\": 525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 382, \"end\": 396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NSW parliament\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_New_South_Wales\"}, {\"begin\": 465, \"end\": 485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macquarie_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1361183932977582e-48, \"text\": \"Macquarie University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macquarie_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macquarie_University\"}, {\"begin\": 511, \"end\": 524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_funeral\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"State funeral\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_funeral\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_funeral\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His ministerial career\", \"from\": 327, \"to\": 349}, {\"ngram\": \"terms\", \"from\": 354, \"to\": 359}, {\"ngram\": \"both houses\", \"from\": 363, \"to\": 374}, {\"ngram\": \"his subsequent achievements\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 436}, {\"ngram\": \"Chancellor\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 461}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Former NSW State Treasurer Michael Egan at Parliament House, 2008.Credit:Fairfax But he decided to be buried simply at the Woronora Memorial Park, Sutherland, adjacent to where his parents are in the Catholic section of the cemetery, with priests at the graveside, but no earthly bother otherwise.\", \"from\": 527, \"to\": 825, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 538, \"end\": 553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pennsylvania_Treasurer\