": 790}, {\"ngram\": \"no earthly bother\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 813}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This had a family precedent.\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 855, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a family precedent\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 854}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When his mother, Jean n\\u00e9e Brown (1923-2016) died, the notice in theHeraldread: \\\"At Jean's insistence, she will be buried without fuss or ceremony and, again at her request, without mourning.\\\"\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 1047, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 878, \"end\": 881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maiden_and_married_names\", \"score\": 0.9989764927117052, \"rank\": 0.0010245559290461407, \"text\": \"n\\u00e9e\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maiden_and_married_names\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maiden_and_married_names\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his mother\", \"from\": 861, \"to\": 871}, {\"ngram\": \"theHeraldread\", \"from\": 920, \"to\": 933}, {\"ngram\": \"Jean's insistence\", \"from\": 939, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"fuss\", \"from\": 985, \"to\": 989}, {\"ngram\": \"ceremony\", \"from\": 993, \"to\": 1001}, {\"ngram\": \"her request\", \"from\": 1016, \"to\": 1027}, {\"ngram\": \"mourning\", \"from\": 1037, \"to\": 1045}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This might imply a shy, retiring disposition at the heart of the family.\", \"from\": 1049, \"to\": 1121, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a shy, retiring disposition\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1093}, {\"ngram\": \"the heart\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1106}, {\"ngram\": \"the family\", \"from\": 1110, \"to\": 1120}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was no such modesty.\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1148, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no such modesty\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1147}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jean, a livewire, dynamic personality, whose fabled fashion shop in Caringbah, and her white house, manicured lawns and sprightly flower decorations on the Kingsway, Cronulla, were landmarks in the Shire.\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1217, \"end\": 1226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caringbah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.868907355554322e-34, \"text\": \"Caringbah\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caringbah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caringbah\"}, {\"begin\": 1315, \"end\": 1323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\", \"score\": 0.9999928296340526, \"rank\": 7.170351116625801e-06, \"text\": \"Cronulla\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jean\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1153}, {\"ngram\": \"a livewire, dynamic personality\", \"from\": 1155, \"to\": 1186}, {\"ngram\": \"whose fabled fashion shop\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1213}, {\"ngram\": \"her white house\", \"from\": 1232, \"to\": 1247}, {\"ngram\": \"lawns\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1264}, {\"ngram\": \"sprightly flower decorations\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1297}, {\"ngram\": \"landmarks\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1339}, {\"ngram\": \"the Shire\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1352}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She lived the motto 'life is celebrated with the living, not the dead'.\", \"from\": 1354, \"to\": 1425, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the motto 'life\", \"from\": 1364, \"to\": 1379}, {\"ngram\": \"the living\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1409}, {\"ngram\": \"the dead\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1423}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Egan was born in Coogee, in Sydney's eastern suburbs, on February 21, 1948, the son of Jean and Stanley Joseph Egan, who served as a sergeant in the Royal Australian Artillery from 1939 to 1948.\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1621, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1444, \"end\": 1450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Electoral_district_of_Coogee\", \"