 \"end\": 1729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999921819835, \"rank\": 7.81559127015288e-09, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a stubborn youngster\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1700}, {\"ngram\": \"Egan\", \"from\": 1702, \"to\": 1706}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reared in Caringbah, then Cronulla, young Egan from third grade onwards went to St Patrick's College, the Christian Brothers school in Sutherland.\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1797, \"end\": 1806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caringbah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.868907355554322e-34, \"text\": \"Caringbah\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caringbah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caringbah\"}, {\"begin\": 1813, \"end\": 1821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\", \"score\": 0.9999928296340526, \"rank\": 7.170351116625801e-06, \"text\": \"Cronulla\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\"}, {\"begin\": 1870, \"end\": 1877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\", \"score\": 0.9991736981203899, \"rank\": 0.0006938065930965277, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\"}, {\"begin\": 1903, \"end\": 1911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brother\", \"score\": 0.9999999949923222, \"rank\": 5.005192842007275e-09, \"text\": \"Brothers\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brother\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brother\"}, {\"begin\": 1922, \"end\": 1932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.410635821738757e-16, \"text\": \"Sutherland\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"young Egan\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 1833}, {\"ngram\": \"third grade\", \"from\": 1839, \"to\": 1850}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He completed a BA at the University of Sydney.\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 1980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1949, \"end\": 1951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bachelor_of_Arts\", \"score\": 0.9999789549969919, \"rank\": 2.1039645919354796e-05, \"text\": \"BA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bachelor_of_Arts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bachelor_of_Arts\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the University\", \"from\": 1955, \"to\": 1969}, {\"ngram\": \"Sydney\", \"from\": 1973, \"to\": 1979}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He joined the ALP in school shorts, in 1964, aged 16.\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 2034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1995, \"end\": 1998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.333104223138619e-67, \"text\": \"ALP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"school shorts\", \"from\": 2002, \"to\": 2015}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Egan was elected MP for Cronulla in 1978, aged thirty, on his fourth attempt (he also stood in 1971, '73, and '76), his parliamentary speeches, interjections, and buoyant turns of phrase, marked him as a future star and a favourite of NSW Premier Neville Wran.\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2301, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2065, \"end\": 2073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\", \"score\": 0.9999928296340526, \"rank\": 7.170351116625801e-06, \"text\": \"Cronulla\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronulla-Sutherland_Sharks\"}, {\"begin\": 2276, \"end\": 2287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Premier_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NSW Premier\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Premier_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Premier_of_New_South_Wales\"}, {\"begin\": 2288, \"end\": 2300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neville_Wran\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Neville Wran\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neville_Wran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neville_Wran\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Egan\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2045}, {\"ngram\": \"MP\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2060}, {\"ngram\": \"his fourth attempt\", \"from\": 2099, \"to\": 2117}, {\"ngram\": \"his parliamentary speeches\", \"from\": 2157, \"to\": 2183}, {\"ngram\": \"interjections\", \"from\": 2185, \"to\": 2198}, {\"ngram\": \"buoyant turns\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2217}, {\"ngram\": \"phrase\", \"from\": 2221, \"to\": 2227}, {\"ngram\": \"a future star\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2256}, {\"ngram\": \"a favourite\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2272}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But in NSW Labor politics, getting ahead is hard scrabble.\", \"from\": 2302, \"to\": 2360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2313, \"end\": 2318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5292916410306297e-51, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He knew luck mattered as well as determination to win friends in the party and beyond.\", \"from\": 2361, \"to\": 2447, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"luck\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2373}, {\"ngram\": \"friends\", \"from\": 2415, \"to\": 2422}, {\"ngram\": \"the party\", \"from\": 2426, \"to\": 2435}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A strong sense of social justice, business acumen, and a flair for the theatrical Egan inherited from his mother.\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2562, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A strong sense\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2463}, {\"ngram\": \"social justice\", \"from\": 2467, \"to\": 2481}, {\"ngram\": \"business acumen\", \"from\": 2483, \"to\": 2498}, {\"ngram\": \"a flair\", \"from\": 2504, \"to\": 2511}, {\"ngram\": \"the theatrical Egan\", \"from\": 2516, \"to\": 2535}, {\"ngram\": \"his mother\", \"from\": 2551, \"to\": 2561}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was an elegant, cheerful, generous, and kindly lady, a single parent after the premature death of her husband.\", \"from\": 2563, \"to\": 2677, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a single parent\", \"from\": 2620, \"to\": 2635}, {\"ngram\": \"the premature death\", \"from\": 2642, \"to\": 2661}, {\"ngram\": \"her husband\", \"from\": 2665, \"to\": 2676}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fit, gifted with dark good looks, curly hair, dominating dark-rim spectacles (in those days), he cut a lithe, hungry look, if a little on the short side.\", \"from\": 2679, \"to\": 2832, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"dark good looks\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2711}, {\"ngram\": \"curly hair\", \"from\": 2713, \"to\": 2723}, {\"ngram\": \"dark-rim spectacles\", \"from\": 2736, \"to\": 2755}, {\"ngram\": \"those days\", \"from\": 2760, \"to\": 2770}, {\"ngram\": \"a lithe, hungry look\", \"from\": 2780, \"to\": 2800}, {\"ngram\": \"the short side\", \"from\": 2817, \"to\": 2831}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 1980s and 1990s, Egan was one of the \\\"big guns\\\" at NSW ALP conferences.\", \"from\": 2833, \"to\": 2911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2891, \"end\": 2894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 1980s\", \"from\": 2836, \"to\": 2845}, {\"ngram\": \"1990s\", \"from\": 2850, \"to\": 2855}, {\"ngram\": \"Egan\", \"from\": 2857, \"to\": 2861}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"big guns\", \"from\": 2873, \"to\": 2886}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Memorably he once said: \\\"The physical distance between having your ear to the ground and your head buried in the sand may not be great, but that difference makes all the difference.\\\"\", \"from\": 2913, \"to\": 3095, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The physical distance\", \"from\": 2938, \"to\": 2959}, {\"ngram\": \"your ear\", \"from\": 2975, \"to\": 2983}, {\"ngram\": \"the ground\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 2997}, {\"ngram\": \"your head\", \"from\": 3002, \"to\": 3011}, {\"ngram\": \"the sand\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3030}, {\"ngram\": \"that difference\", \"from\": 3053, \"to\": 3068}, {\"ngram\": \"all the difference\", \"from\": 3075, \"to\": 3093}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One measure of his career is that Egan was always mindful of that insight.\", \"from\": 3096, \"to\": 3170, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One measure\", \"from\": 3096, \"to\": 3107}, {\"ngram\": \"his career\", \"from\": 3111, \"to\": 3121}, {\"ngram\": \"Egan\", \"from\": 3130, \"to\": 3134}, {\"ngram\": \"that insight\", \"from\": 3157, \"to\": 3169}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Egan began active politics on the ALP Left, thinking the party's head office too conservative, but he never had any allegiance to Marxist elements in the ALP, and from the start he was instinctively wary of local Labor supremo (and alleged secret communist) Arthur Gietzelt, who dominated Shire politics back in the day.\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3302, \"end\": 3309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marxism\", \"score\": 0.9990395928223224, \"rank\": 0.0009613304460498817, \"text\": \"Marxist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marxism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marxism\"}, {\"begin\": 3326, \"end\": 3329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.333104223138619e-67, \"text\": \"ALP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 3385, \"end\": 3390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5292916410306297e-51, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 3430, \"end\": 3436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_Arthur\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.874693427474453e-12, \"text\": \"Arthur\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_Arthur\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_Arthur\"}, {\"begin\": 3461, \"end\": 3466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.249000429859319e-22, \"text\": \"Shire\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Egan\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3176}, {\"ngram\": \"active politics\", \"from\": 3183, \"to\": 3198}, {\"ngram\": \"the ALP Left\", \"from\": 3202, \"to\": 3214}, {\"ngram\": \"the party's head office\", \"from\": 3225, \"to\": 3248}, {\"ngram\": \"any allegiance\", \"from\": 3284, \"to\": 3298}, {\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 3340, \"to\": 3349}, {\"ngram\": \"alleged secret communist\", \"from\": 3404, \"to\": 3428}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 3484, \"to\": 3491}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Employed as an Industrial Officer in the national office of the Australasian Meat Industries Employees Association, he was in good company.\", \"from\": 3494, \"to\": 3633, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an Industrial Officer\", \"from\": 3506, \"to\": 3527}, {\"ngram\": \"the national office\", \"from\": 3531, \"to\": 3550}, {\"ngram\": \"the Australasian Meat Industries Employees Association\", \"from\": 3554, \"to\": 3608}, {\"ngram\": \"good company\", \"from\": 3620, \"to\": 3632}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Future Keating staffer and noted journalist John Edwards, author of acclaimed biographies of Curtin and Keating, was a contemporary, also for a time employed by 'the meaties'.\", \"from\": 3634, \"to\": 3809, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3727, \"end\": 3733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Curtin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9990971609732295e-16, \"text\": \"Curtin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Curtin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Curtin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Future Keating staffer\", \"from\": 3634, \"to\": 3656}, {\"ngram\": \"noted journalist John Edwards\", \"from\": 3661, \"to\": 3690}, {\"ngram\": \"author\", \"from\": 3692, \"to\": 3698}, {\"ngram\": \"acclaimed biographies\", \"from\": 3702, \"to\": 3723}, {\"ngram\": \"Keating\", \"from\": 3738, \"to\": 3745}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 3776, \"to\": 3782}, {\"ngram\": \"the meaties\", \"from\": 3796, \"to\": 3807}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the Whitlam years, until the government's defeat, Egan worked with Les Johnson, MP for Hughes, an electorate then based on Sutherland and surrounding suburbs.\", \"from\": 3811, \"to\": 3972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3881, \"end\": 3892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Johnson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.902333021494056e-21, \"text\": \"Les Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Johnson\"}, {\"begin\": 3901, \"end\": 3907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billy_Hughes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.676322013342198e-25, \"text\": \"Hughes\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billy_Hughes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billy_Hughes\"}, {\"begin\": 3937, \"end\": 3947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.410635821738757e-16, \"text\": \"Sutherland\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sutherland_Shire\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Whitlam years\", \"from\": 3814, \"to\": 3831}, {\"ngram\": \"the government's defeat\", \"from\": 3839, \"to\": 3862}, {\"ngram\": \"Egan\", \"from\": 3864, \"to\": 3868}, {\"ngram\": \"MP\", \"from\": 3894, \"to\": 3896}, {\"ngram\": \"an electorate\", \"from\": 3909, \"to\": 3922}, {\"ngram\": \"surrounding suburbs\", \"from\": 3952, \"to\": 3971}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then came public service, as a complaints officer in the State Pollution Control Commission.\", \"from\": 3973, \"to\": 4065, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"public service\", \"from\": 3983, \"to\": 3997}, {\"ngram\": \"a complaints officer\", \"from\": 4002, \"to\": 4022}, {\"ngram\": \"the State Pollution Control Commission\", \"from\": 4026, \"to\": 4064}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Involvement in politics taught him to greatly respect Whitlam's contribution and almost seamlessly he came to identify with the NSW Right, believing the best of that tradition lay in innovative, practical, reforms, alert to public sentiment as well as seized by the determination to make a difference to ordinary people's lives.\", \"from\": 4067, \"to\": 4395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4121, \"end\": 4128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gough_Whitlam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.158420965161067e-20, \"text\": \"Whitlam\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gough_Whitlam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gough_Whitlam\"}, {\"begin\": 4195, \"end\": 4198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Involvement\", \"from\": 4067, \"to\": 4078}, {\"ngram\": \"politics\", \"from\": 4082, \"to\": 4090}, {\"ngram\": \"that tradition\", \"from\": 4228, \"to\": 4242}, {\"ngram\": \"innovative, practical, reforms\", \"from\": 4250, \"to\": 4280}, {\"ngram\": \"public sentiment\", \"from\": 4291, \"to\": 4307}, {\"ngram\": \"the determination\", \"from\": 4329, \"to\": 4346}, {\"ngram\": \"a difference\", \"from\": 4355, \"to\": 4367}, {\"ngram\": \"ordinary people's lives\", \"from\": 4371, \"to\": 4394}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Treasurer Michael Egan announces the commencement of construction for the $225 million Master Plan redevelopments at Taronga and Western Plains Zoos, 2002.Credit:Fairfax He believed personal leadership mattered.\", \"from\": 4397, \"to\": 4609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4407, \"end\": 4419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2469837578729036e-16, \"text\": \"Michael Egan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\"}, {\"begin\": 4559, \"end\": 4566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.546278550098478e-20, \"text\": \"Fairfax\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the commencement\", \"from\": 4430, \"to\": 4446}, {\"ngram\": \"construction\", \"from\": 4450, \"to\": 4462}, {\"ngram\": \"the $225 million Master Plan redevelopments\", \"from\": 4467, \"to\": 4510}, {\"ngram\": \"Taronga and Western Plains Zoos\", \"from\": 4514, \"to\": 4545}, {\"ngram\": \"personal leadership\", \"from\": 4579, \"to\": 4598}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In one of his first speeches in the NSW parliament, he said ministers had to take responsibility for their actions, and not hide behind public servants: \\\"The task of a minister is \\u2026to make the difficult decisions of government, [not] to leave them to independent public servants while he jumps up and down on the back seat of a ministerial car.\\\"\", \"from\": 4610, \"to\": 4955, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4646, \"end\": 4660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NSW parliament\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_New_South_Wales\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his first speeches\", \"from\": 4620, \"to\": 4638}, {\"ngram\": \"ministers\", \"from\": 4670, \"to\": 4679}, {\"ngram\": \"responsibility\", \"from\": 4692, \"to\": 4706}, {\"ngram\": \"their actions\", \"from\": 4711, \"to\": 4724}, {\"ngram\": \"public servants\", \"from\": 4746, \"to\": 4761}, {\"ngram\": \"The task\", \"from\": 4764, \"to\": 4772}, {\"ngram\": \"a minister\", \"from\": 4776, \"to\": 4786}, {\"ngram\": \"the difficult decisions\", \"from\": 4799, \"to\": 4822}, {\"ngram\": \"government\", \"from\": 4826, \"to\": 4836}, {\"ngram\": \"independent public servants\", \"from\": 4861, \"to\": 4888}, {\"ngram\": \"the back seat\", \"from\": 4919, \"to\": 4932}, {\"ngram\": \"a ministerial car\", \"from\": 4936, \"to\": 4953}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He had the gift of the gab, the verbal jab too, but was good-humoured and, mostly, widely respected across both sides of his politics, with the ALP Left, and with his Liberal and National party opponents.\", \"from\": 4957, \"to\": 5161, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the gift\", \"from\": 4964, \"to\": 4972}, {\"ngram\": \"the gab\", \"from\": 4976, \"to\": 4983}, {\"ngram\": \"the verbal jab\", \"from\": 4985, \"to\": 4999}, {\"ngram\": \"both sides\", \"from\": 5064, \"to\": 5074}, {\"ngram\": \"his politics\", \"from\": 5078, \"to\": 5090}, {\"ngram\": \"the ALP Left\", \"from\": 5097, \"to\": 5109}, {\"ngram\": \"his Liberal and National party opponents\", \"from\": 5120, \"to\": 5160}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From 1981 to 1984 as chair of the NSW Public Accounts Committee, Egan authored landmark reports on, and audit reviews of, government programs.\", \"from\": 5163, \"to\": 5305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5197, \"end\": 5200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}, {\"begin\": 5201, \"end\": 5226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Public_accounts_committee\", \"score\": 0.9999611130136701, \"rank\": 3.8888498342307806e-05, \"tex