"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\"}, {\"begin\": 5702, \"end\": 5717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barrie_Unsworth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barrie Unsworth\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barrie_Unsworth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barrie_Unsworth\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the budget\", \"from\": 5633, \"to\": 5643}, {\"ngram\": \"1995.Credit\", \"from\": 5645, \"to\": 5656}, {\"ngram\": \"a great mentor\", \"from\": 5726, \"to\": 5740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Selected to invigorate Labor in the Upper House, he served in the NSW Legislative Council beginning in 1986.\", \"from\": 5743, \"to\": 5851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5766, \"end\": 5771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5292916410306297e-51, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 5779, \"end\": 5790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Senate\", \"score\": 0.9998654330011266, \"rank\": 0.0001345851094959585, \"text\": \"Upper House\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Senate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Senate\"}, {\"begin\": 5809, \"end\": 5832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Legislative_Council\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NSW Legislative Council\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Legislative_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Legislative_Council\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bob Carr was one of his champions.\", \"from\": 5852, \"to\": 5886, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5852, \"end\": 5855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"score\": 0.9993124870684011, \"rank\": 0.0006878034058488228, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his champions\", \"from\": 5872, \"to\": 5885}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In opposition Egan, in a daring act of invention styled himself as the \\\"Chair of the NSW Waste Watch Committee\\\", getting much more attention than any of the sleepy performers among his colleagues.\", \"from\": 5888, \"to\": 6084, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"opposition Egan\", \"from\": 5891, \"to\": 5906}, {\"ngram\": \"a daring act\", \"from\": 5911, \"to\": 5923}, {\"ngram\": \"invention\", \"from\": 5927, \"to\": 5936}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"Chair\", \"from\": 5955, \"to\": 5965}, {\"ngram\": \"the NSW Waste Watch Committee\", \"from\": 5969, \"to\": 5998}, {\"ngram\": \"much more attention\", \"from\": 6009, \"to\": 6028}, {\"ngram\": \"the sleepy performers\", \"from\": 6041, \"to\": 6062}, {\"ngram\": \"his colleagues\", \"from\": 6069, \"to\": 6083}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That role attracted great media attention in his imaginative criticisms of the then Greiner and Fahey governments.\", \"from\": 6086, \"to\": 6200, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That role\", \"from\": 6086, \"to\": 6095}, {\"ngram\": \"great media attention\", \"from\": 6106, \"to\": 6127}, {\"ngram\": \"his imaginative criticisms\", \"from\": 6131, \"to\": 6157}, {\"ngram\": \"the then Greiner and Fahey governments\", \"from\": 6161, \"to\": 6199}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1990, he was narrowly defeated in a ballot of colleagues as Deputy Leader of Labor in the Legislative Council.\", \"from\": 6201, \"to\": 6314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6294, \"end\": 6313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Legislative_Council\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.744881372490074e-23, \"text\": \"Legislative Council\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Legislative_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Legislative_Council\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a ballot\", \"from\": 6238, \"to\": 6246}, {\"ngram\": \"colleagues\", \"from\": 6250, \"to\": 6260}, {\"ngram\": \"Deputy Leader\", \"from\": 6264, \"to\": 6277}, {\"ngram\": \"Labor\", \"from\": 6281, \"to\": 6286}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1991, however, he was clearly the deserving leader of the ALP, and Leader of the Opposition, in the Chamber.\", \"from\": 6315, \"to\": 6426, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6376, \"end\": 6379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.333104223138619e-67, \"text\": \"ALP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the deserving leader\", \"from\": 6348, \"to\": 6368}, {\"ngram\": \"Leader\", \"from\": 6385, \"to\": 6391}, {\"ngram\": \"the Opposition\", \"from\": 6395, \"to\": 6409}, {\"ngram\": \"the Chamber\", \"from\": 6414, \"to\": 6425}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Everything seemed to prepare him for the most important role of his life, NSW treasurer, which he took on when Bob Carr led Labor to victory in 1995.\", \"from\": 6428, \"to\": 6577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6502, \"end\": 6505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}, {\"begin\": 6539, \"end\": 6542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"score\": 0.9993124870684011, \"rank\": 0.0006878034058488228, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\"}, {\"begin\": 6552, \"end\": 6557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5292916410306297e-51, \"text\": \"Labor\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Everything\", \"from\": 6428, \"to\": 6438}, {\"ngram\": \"the most important role\", \"from\": 6465, \"to\": 6488}, {\"ngram\": \"his life\", \"from\": 6492, \"to\": 6500}, {\"ngram\": \"victory\", \"from\": 6561, \"to\": 6568}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Treasurer Michael Egan addressing the journalists about the budget, 1999.Credit:Fairfax Treasury officials admired his hands-on management, which drew on the talent around him, and in a probing, collegiate manner, he asked questions as to how the state's resources could be better managed.\", \"from\": 6579, \"to\": 6869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6589, \"end\": 6601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2469837578729036e-16, \"text\": \"Michael Egan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\"}, {\"begin\": 6659, \"end\": 6666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.546278550098478e-20, \"text\": \"Fairfax\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\"}, {\"begin\": 6668, \"end\": 6676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Treasury\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.799924981749297e-16, \"text\": \"Treasury\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Treasury\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Treasury\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the journalists\", \"from\": 6613, \"to\": 6628}, {\"ngram\": \"the budget\", \"from\": 6635, \"to\": 6645}, {\"ngram\": \"his hands-on management\", \"from\": 6694, \"to\": 6717}, {\"ngram\": \"the talent\", \"from\": 6733, \"to\": 6743}, {\"ngram\": \"a probing, collegiate manner\", \"from\": 6763, \"to\": 6791}, {\"ngram\": \"questions\", \"from\": 6802, \"to\": 6811}, {\"ngram\": \"the state's resources\", \"from\": 6822, \"to\": 6843}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was ably assisted by a strong ministerial staff and Egan personally sponsored the public service career of Michael Coutts-Trotter, who went on to be Secretary of Premier & Cabinet, as well as, now, secretary to the NSW Treasury.\", \"from\": 6870, \"to\": 7101, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6980, \"end\": 7002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Coutts-Trotter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michael Coutts-Trotter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Coutts-Trotter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Coutts-Trotter\"}, {\"begin\": 7088, \"end\": 7100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Treasury\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NSW Treasury\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Treasury\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales_Treasury\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a strong ministerial staff\", \"from\": 6894, \"to\": 6920}, {\"ngram\": \"Egan\", \"from\": 6925, \"to\": 6929}, {\"ngram\": \"the public service career\", \"from\": 6951, \"to\": 6976}, {\"ngram\": \"Secretary\", \"from\": 7022, \"to\": 7031}, {\"ngram\": \"Premier\", \"from\": 7035, \"to\": 7042}, {\"ngram\": \"Cabinet\", \"from\": 7045, \"to\": 7052}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As treasurer in the Carr government, Egan was responsible for safeguarding NSW's AAA credit rating.\", \"from\": 7103, \"to\": 7202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7178, \"end\": 7181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}, {\"begin\": 7184, \"end\": 7187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Automobile_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999687590730632, \"rank\": 3.123488957870851e-05, \"text\": \"AAA\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Automobile_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Automobile_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"treasurer\", \"from\": 7106, \"to\": 7115}, {\"ngram\": \"the Carr government\", \"from\": 7119, \"to\": 7138}, {\"ngram\": \"Egan\", \"from\": 7140, \"to\": 7144}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He relentlessly focused on introducing market tests for government enterprises.\", \"from\": 7203, \"to\": 7282, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"market tests\", \"from\": 7242, \"to\": 7254}, {\"ngram\": \"government enterprises\", \"from\": 7259, \"to\": 7281}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He delivered nine balanced budgets on a net lending basis, eliminated government net debt and fully funded the Sydney Olympics.\", \"from\": 7283, \"to\": 7410, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nine balanced budgets\", \"from\": 7296, \"to\": 7317}, {\"ngram\": \"a net lending basis\", \"from\": 7321, \"to\": 7340}, {\"ngram\": \"government net debt\", \"from\": 7353, \"to\": 7372}, {\"ngram\": \"the Sydney Olympics\", \"from\": 7390, \"to\": 7409}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not everything went smoothly, but Egan is remembered as the engine of reform innovation in the NSW government.\", \"from\": 7412, \"to\": 7522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7507, \"end\": 7510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Not everything\", \"from\": 7412, \"to\": 7426}, {\"ngram\": \"Egan\", \"from\": 7446, \"to\": 7450}, {\"ngram\": \"the engine\", \"from\": 7468, \"to\": 7478}, {\"ngram\": \"reform innovation\", \"from\": 7482, \"to\": 7499}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He favoured electricity privatisation in Carr's first term, but union opposition put a stop to what he saw for NSW a lucrative bargain: high prices for selling electricity generation assets in exchange for reinvesting in transport and social infrastructure.\", \"from\": 7523, \"to\": 7780, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7634, \"end\": 7637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"electricity privatisation\", \"from\": 7535, \"to\": 7560}, {\"ngram\": \"Carr's first term\", \"from\": 7564, \"to\": 7581}, {\"ngram\": \"union opposition\", \"from\": 7587, \"to\": 7603}, {\"ngram\": \"a stop\", \"from\": 7608, \"to\": 7614}, {\"ngram\": \"a lucrative bargain\", \"from\": 7638, \"to\": 7657}, {\"ngram\": \"high prices\", \"from\": 7659, \"to\": 7670}, {\"ngram\": \"electricity generation assets\", \"from\": 7683, \"to\": 7712}, {\"ngram\": \"exchange\", \"from\": 7716, \"to\": 7724}, {\"ngram\": \"transport\", \"from\": 7744, \"to\": 7753}, {\"ngram\": \"social infrastructure\", \"from\": 7758, \"to\": 7779}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He supported Premier Morris Iemma's abortive efforts along the same lines in 2008.\", \"from\": 7782, \"to\": 7864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7803, \"end\": 7815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Iemma\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Morris Iemma\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Iemma\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Iemma\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the same lines\", \"from\": 7841, \"to\": 7855}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Egan always thought: \\\"if we do not do this, the Tories will.\", \"from\": 7865, \"to\": 7925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7913, \"end\": 7919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6514773368375486e-15, \"text\": \"Tories\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Egan\", \"from\": 7865, \"to\": 7869}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And they will skewer the priorities away from where it matters most.\\\"\", \"from\": 7926, \"to\": 7995, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the priorities\", \"from\": 7947, \"to\": 7961}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Demonstration against the proposed Michael Egan tax on poker machines in NSW clubs in the city, 2003.Credit:Fairfax In frustration, he resigned from the ALP when John Robertson became NSW opposition leader in 2011 and rejoined when \\\"Robbo\\\" lost his role in 2014.\", \"from\": 7997, \"to\": 8260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8032, \"end\": 8044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2469837578729036e-16, \"text\": \"Michael Egan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Francis_Egan\"}, {\"begin\": 8070, \"end\": 8073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9955039072038111, \"rank\": 0.004516398944938377, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_New_South_Wales\"}, {\"begin\": 8105, \"end\": 8112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.546278550098478e-20, \"text\": \"Fairfax\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\"}, {\"begin\": 8151, \"end\": 8154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.333104223138619e-67, \"text\": \"ALP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Labor_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 8160, \"end\": 8174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_S._Robertson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.877260998301341e-14, \"text\": \"John Robertson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_S._Robertson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_S._Robertson\"}, {\"begin\": 8182, \"end\": 8203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leader_of_the_Opposition_(New_South_Wales)\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NSW opposition leader\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leader_of_the_Opposition_(New_South_Wales)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leader_of_the_Opposition_(New_South_Wales)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"poker machines\", \"from\": 8052, \"to\": 8066}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 8083, \"to\": 8091}, {\"ngram\": \"frustration\", \"from\": 8116, \"to\": 8127}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Robbo\", \"from\": 8229, \"to\": 8235}, {\"ngram\": \"his role\", \"from\": 8242, \"to\": 8250}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Egan was still smarting over Robinson's actions in 2001, when the latter was secretary of Unions NSW.\", \"from\": 8261, \"to\": 8362, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8290, \"end\": 8298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Robinson\", \"score\": 0.9719854895945259, \"rank\": 0.02880839232989489, \"text\": \"Robinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Robinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Robinson\"}, {\"begin\": 8351, \"end\": 8361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Labor_Council_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Unions NSW\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q178790\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Labor_Council_of_New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Labor_Council_of_New_South_Wales\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Egan\", \"from\": 8261, \"to\": 8265}, {\"ngram\": \"secretary\", \"from\": 8338, \"to\": 8347}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At that time, Robertson led a blockade of the NSW parliament over workers' compensation law reforms.\", \"from\": 8364, \"to\": 8464, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8378, \"end\": 8387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Division_of_Robertson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7856593650651004e-22, \"text\": \"Robertson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Division_of_Robertson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Division_of_Robertson\"}, {\"begin\": 8410, \"end\": 8424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \