ngram\": \"completion\", \"from\": 8673, \"to\": 8683}, {\"ngram\": \"the spires\", \"from\": 8687, \"to\": 8697}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 8724, \"to\": 8728}, {\"ngram\": \"the Bicentennial\", \"from\": 8732, \"to\": 8748}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But His Eminence hesitated, preferring a public appeal from parishioners, emphasising the building was built from the pennies and threepences donated by the working poor.\", \"from\": 8751, \"to\": 8921, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His Eminence\", \"from\": 8755, \"to\": 8767}, {\"ngram\": \"a public appeal\", \"from\": 8790, \"to\": 8805}, {\"ngram\": \"parishioners\", \"from\": 8811, \"to\": 8823}, {\"ngram\": \"the building\", \"from\": 8837, \"to\": 8849}, {\"ngram\": \"the pennies\", \"from\": 8865, \"to\": 8876}, {\"ngram\": \"threepences\", \"from\": 8881, \"to\": 8892}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Egan was Treasurer, the Expenditure Review Committee of Cabinet granted $5m to cover the outstanding funding deficit, matching funds already raised, to enable the spires to be finally completed in 2000.\", \"from\": 8922, \"to\": 9129, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Egan\", \"from\": 8927, \"to\": 8931}, {\"ngram\": \"Treasurer\", \"from\": 8936, \"to\": 8945}, {\"ngram\": \"the Expenditure Review Committee\", \"from\": 8947, \"to\": 8979}, {\"ngram\": \"Cabinet\", \"from\": 8983, \"to\": 8990}, {\"ngram\": \"the outstanding funding deficit\", \"from\": 9012, \"to\": 9043}, {\"ngram\": \"matching funds\", \"from\": 9045, \"to\": 9059}, {\"ngram\": \"the spires\", \"from\": 9086, \"to\": 9096}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The back-to-school bonus that Premier Unsworth tried to introduce in 1987 and resisted in Cabinet, was then introduced by Egan with little fanfare in 1995, in his first Budget.\", \"from\": 9131, \"to\": 9307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9169, \"end\": 9177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barrie_Unsworth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.235177088259642e-57, \"text\